citations:
    citation-affc-the-krakens-daughter-i:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "The Kraken's Daughter"
            text_from_source: "Was my father murdered? / So your mother believes. / And what does my nuncle believe? / Balon fell to his death when a rope bridge broke beneath him. A storm was rising, and the bridge was swaying and twisting with each gust of wind. Or so we are told."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Asha Greyjoy. Chapter title: The Kraken's Daughter. Asha arrives at Ten Towers on Harlaw aboard Black Wind, with Lady Glover and her children as captives from Deepwood Motte. She consults with her uncle Lord Rodrik Harlaw (the Reader), who warns her the kingsmoot will not choose her. Aeron Damphair has called the kingsmoot on Old Wyk. Asha visits her mother Lady Alannys Harlaw (née Harlaw), who is feeble and asks for news of Theon. Asha decides to attend the kingsmoot despite Rodrik's warnings. Introduces: Lord Rodrik Harlaw (reader, lord of Ten Towers), Lady Gwynesse Harlaw (Rodrik's eldest sister, widowed, lives at Ten Towers claiming it is hers), Lady Alannys Harlaw (Asha's mother, Balon's widow), Three-Tooth (steward of Ten Towers), Tristifer Botley (Tris), Lady Glover and her children (captives). House Harlaw's branches: Boremund the Blue at Harridan Hill, Sigfryd Silverhair at Harlaw Hall, Hotho Harlaw (humpback) at Tower of Glimmering, Ser Harras Harlaw (the Knight) at Grey Garden. Confirms Balon's death is suspicious — Euron arrived within a day."
